# Azure Container Apps deployment sketch

```bash
az login
az group create -n rg-tb-spread -l westeurope
az acr create -g rg-tb-spread -n <your_acr_name> --sku Basic
az acr login -n <your_acr_name>

docker build -t <your_acr_name>.azurecr.io/tb-spread-dashboard:latest .
docker push <your_acr_name>.azurecr.io/tb-spread-dashboard:latest

az containerapp env create \
  -g rg-tb-spread \
  -n cae-tb-spread \
  -l westeurope

az containerapp create \
  -g rg-tb-spread \
  -n tb-spread-dashboard \
  --environment cae-tb-spread \
  --image <your_acr_name>.azurecr.io/tb-spread-dashboard:latest \
  --target-port 8501 \
  --ingress external \
  --registry-server <your_acr_name>.azurecr.io \
  --min-replicas 1 \
  --max-replicas 2
```

For production, add a scheduled collector that writes Parquet snapshots to Blob Storage and let Streamlit read cached files first.
